<div class = 'definitionBox'>
    <h5>
        Newton's First Law:
    </h5>
    <p>
        An object at rest will stay at rest unless acted upon by a net outside force.
        An object in motion will stay in motion unless acted upon by a net outside force.
    </p>
</div>

<div class = 'definitionBox'>
    <h5>
        Inertia:
    </h5>
    <p>
        One way of reading Newton’s First Law is that objects will resist any change in their motion.
        If they are not moving, it requires a force to make them start moving.
        If they are moving, it requires a force to make an object stop, to move faster,
        or to change its direction.
    </p>
    <p>
        This resistance of a change in motion is called an object’s inertia.
        The more mass an object has, the more inertia it has!
    </p>
</div>

